                    </div>
                    <span>You don't have to be a cyclist to appreciate the thrills and suspense in Dave Shields's novel The<BR>Race. From the opening paragraphs, you'll find yourself caught up in the excitement of Ben<BR>Barnes's experiences, from wobbly boy on his first bicycle to contender in the Tour de France.<BR>More than a heart-stopping introduction to the world of competitive cycling, The Race is also a<BR>coming-of-age story about a truly deserving hero. You'll cheer to see that nice guys don't have to<BR>finish last.</span>
                  
              
